-- Monte dei Paschi shares up as top executives stay on
-- 
-- Wed Jan 15, 2014 03:15AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Jan 15 (Reuters) - Shares in Italy's No.3 bank Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI> opened up nearly 3 percent after Chairman Alessandro Profumo and CEO Fabrizio Viola decided to stay on even after being forced to delay a vital 3 billion euro ($4.11 billion) capital increase.

